WEBVTT

00:03:03.383 --> 00:03:05.518
Those who don't work, don't eat.

00:03:05.785 --> 00:03:08.521
Go find your own food.

00:03:09.322 --> 00:03:13.226
Me? I'm okay. Women are grand by birth.

00:03:23.903 --> 00:03:25.405
"Three million."

00:03:25.905 --> 00:03:28.608
Well, I'll have the guys earn it for me.

00:03:31.878 --> 00:03:35.515
Damn, blues harp music is good.
It's just as good as I thought.

00:03:35.982 --> 00:03:37.884
I thought you were a fan of jazz music?

00:03:38.551 --> 00:03:39.485
Don't be stupid.

00:03:39.953 --> 00:03:44.257
I even warbled
when I was sucking on my mother's milk.

00:03:44.691 --> 00:03:46.459
You were a pretty thoughtful kid.

00:03:49.896 --> 00:03:51.764
No mistake... that's Giraffe.

00:03:52.432 --> 00:03:56.236
All right, I'm going from the right.
You go from the left.

00:03:56.903 --> 00:03:58.371
There's a fatso in the way.

00:03:59.872 --> 00:04:02.609
That's... Fatty.

00:04:03.676 --> 00:04:05.011
The ball's in your court.

00:04:07.614 --> 00:04:08.781
Hey, Fatty!

00:04:09.582 --> 00:04:11.851
Fatty River! Long time no see!

00:04:11.918 --> 00:04:15.622
Oh, who'd have thought? It's Jet Black!

00:04:15.688 --> 00:04:17.757
When the hell did you get here?

00:04:18.024 --> 00:04:20.326
How about you? You look so easygoing!

00:04:20.693 --> 00:04:22.562
Did you catch a big one?

00:04:25.665 --> 00:04:28.468
I didn't know you were a fan
of blues music.

00:04:28.534 --> 00:04:29.902
Are you kidding me?

00:04:30.570 --> 00:04:34.907
I've lived only for the blues
since I was in my dad's sack!

00:05:50.917 --> 00:05:52.118
Give him back!

00:05:53.753 --> 00:05:54.987
Zebra!

00:06:32.558 --> 00:06:34.494
Hey, you. Don't die. Hey.

00:06:35.061 --> 00:06:38.030
Shit, are you going to wipe out my bounty?

00:06:38.698 --> 00:06:42.668
D-- Don't be fooled by his appearance.

00:06:42.935 --> 00:06:44.737
You idiot. Don't speak.

00:06:45.738 --> 00:06:50.510
Him... Help... him.

00:06:53.079 --> 00:06:54.447
This stone.

00:07:01.187 --> 00:07:02.054
Hey!

00:07:28.080 --> 00:07:32.585
I can't say for sure until I analyze it,
but it might be worth a hefty sum.

00:07:33.152 --> 00:07:34.954
So, what are you gonna do?

00:07:35.021 --> 00:07:36.189
Like I know.

00:07:36.956 --> 00:07:39.659
He's the one who gave it to me
and he's the one who died.

00:07:39.959 --> 00:07:41.661
I see no harm in keeping it.

00:07:41.727 --> 00:07:42.962
There is no harm.

00:07:43.796 --> 00:07:46.065
After all, it's not your duty
to help the kid.

00:07:47.767 --> 00:07:51.504
This is gonna pay for our food.
There's none for you.

00:07:52.472 --> 00:07:54.474
You have such a poor heart.

00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:56.542
I'm not like that.

00:07:56.876 --> 00:07:58.244
Here, have a gift.

00:07:58.511 --> 00:07:59.946
Oh, what's this?

00:08:02.515 --> 00:08:04.984
An invoice? What for?

00:08:05.551 --> 00:08:08.588
All the expenses that you've racked up
on our ship.

00:08:08.888 --> 00:08:10.223
Thanks for your business.

00:08:10.790 --> 00:08:12.091
You're welcome.

00:08:14.560 --> 00:08:16.896
So, why are you asking about
the dead bounty?

00:08:16.963 --> 00:08:17.864
Well...

00:08:20.132 --> 00:08:22.134
So, you were after Giraffe, too.

00:08:23.202 --> 00:08:24.737
You got a good deal.

00:08:27.874 --> 00:08:29.075
Go ahead, eat.

00:08:29.141 --> 00:08:32.211
Oh, well, there's no bounty in it anyway.

00:08:32.912 --> 00:08:35.014
Yeah. No gain at all.

00:08:36.148 --> 00:08:38.284
No, no. There really is nothing.

00:08:38.851 --> 00:08:41.921
Oh, well, you'll owe me one for today.

00:08:41.988 --> 00:08:45.691
You know that kid on the blues harp
the other day?

00:08:46.592 --> 00:08:49.161
Giraffe was after
that kid, Wenn's, father.

00:08:49.529 --> 00:08:50.897
His old acquaintance, Zebra.

00:08:50.963 --> 00:08:52.098
Acquaintance?

00:08:52.632 --> 00:08:54.000
You didn't know that?

00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:58.137
That they were the top
of the Volunteer Self Defense Squad

00:08:58.204 --> 00:09:00.072
until ten years ago?

00:09:01.941 --> 00:09:06.045
<i>But... why is he after an old comrade?</i>

00:09:08.214 --> 00:09:14.587
<i>Ten years ago, Zebra and Giraffe attempted</i>
<i>to reclaim a certain facility.</i>

00:09:15.087 --> 00:09:18.591
<i>But, a few days later,</i>
<i>Zebra ends up missing</i>

00:09:18.658 --> 00:09:23.796
<i>and Giraffe finds himself blindfolded</i>
<i>in a weird place he'd never seen before.</i>

00:09:26.799 --> 00:09:30.803
<i>Giraffe was going after the top spot</i>
<i>in the group, but he was betrayed.</i>

00:09:31.704 --> 00:09:35.207
<i>But... Zebra was still alive.</i>

00:09:46.118 --> 00:09:50.122
So, in the end, Giraffe was killed
by some form of betrayal?

00:09:50.189 --> 00:09:54.594
Women easily betray others,
but men live for duty.

00:09:55.227 --> 00:09:56.095
Duty, huh?

00:09:56.829 --> 00:09:58.831
That's what I'd like to believe.

00:10:27.727 --> 00:10:29.095
Who are you?

00:10:31.263 --> 00:10:32.398
Someone suspicious.

00:10:33.799 --> 00:10:34.767
What do you want?

00:10:35.234 --> 00:10:38.971
Giraffe asked me to help you.

00:10:43.009 --> 00:10:45.177
But Zebra shot Giraffe.

00:10:45.778 --> 00:10:46.712
Yeah.

00:10:48.280 --> 00:10:51.384
Then why did Giraffe tell him
to help the kid?

00:10:53.152 --> 00:10:54.754
This kid's showing up here, too.

00:10:55.321 --> 00:10:56.922
He must be pretty famous.

00:10:57.189 --> 00:10:59.892
Yeah, the kid's a genius.

00:11:03.863 --> 00:11:06.399
-This guy isn't Zebra!
-What?!

00:11:07.033 --> 00:11:08.968
Look... the date.

00:11:09.902 --> 00:11:10.836
What the--?

00:11:11.303 --> 00:11:15.107
Why the hell is this kid in an article
from 30 years ago, with the same face?!

00:11:16.776 --> 00:11:18.744
Come on. There's nothing to fear.

00:11:19.745 --> 00:11:20.780
Come over here.

00:11:23.983 --> 00:11:25.818
Little twerps should stay out of this.

00:11:27.286 --> 00:11:31.457
If you stick your neck in too far,
you'll get burnt.

00:11:35.061 --> 00:11:37.129
Don't give me that conceited crap, kid.

00:11:37.296 --> 00:11:38.431
I ain't a kid.

00:11:39.198 --> 00:11:40.399
All kids say that.

00:11:42.368 --> 00:11:46.972
I may look like this,
but I've been alive since the days

00:11:47.039 --> 00:11:49.341
when humans only crawled
on the face of the Earth.

00:13:37.049 --> 00:13:40.052
<i>It started on the day</i>
<i>of the accidental explosion</i>

00:13:40.119 --> 00:13:41.554
<i>of the hyperspace gate.</i>

00:13:42.221 --> 00:13:45.024
My body has ceased to age.

00:13:46.492 --> 00:13:47.826
I can't die.

00:13:48.827 --> 00:13:51.530
The guys that took interest in me,
and experimented on me,

00:13:51.597 --> 00:13:53.098
all died before me.

00:13:54.099 --> 00:13:56.869
The end for this guy started
when he snuck into the lab.

00:13:57.369 --> 00:14:01.974
I needed... a parent to use as a cover.

00:14:03.275 --> 00:14:07.346
<i>D-- Don't be fooled by his appearance.</i>

00:14:09.048 --> 00:14:09.915
<i>Him...</i>

00:14:11.050 --> 00:14:14.320
<i>Help... him.</i>

00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:20.359
I think this was the third guy.

00:14:21.527 --> 00:14:22.928
Now, give me the ring.

00:14:23.462 --> 00:14:25.631
Ring? What ring?

00:14:28.133 --> 00:14:29.134
That's fine.

00:14:30.202 --> 00:14:33.172
Even if you had it,
it's a pearl before swine.

00:15:46.111 --> 00:15:49.315
Give me a break, you big klutz.

00:15:49.982 --> 00:15:52.351
You're lucky you got away
with so little...

00:15:53.052 --> 00:15:55.321
since we don't have the money
for a funeral.

00:15:56.355 --> 00:15:57.222
Sorry.

00:16:02.528 --> 00:16:03.729
Knock it off, Ein.

00:16:04.396 --> 00:16:05.431
Shut up.

00:16:20.012 --> 00:16:21.714
Jet, the alpha-catch.

00:16:30.122 --> 00:16:32.324
Shit. This piece of junk.

00:16:33.425 --> 00:16:34.293
All right.

00:16:35.027 --> 00:16:37.262
Now, what are you seeing?

00:16:41.400 --> 00:16:42.267
The hotel.

00:16:43.102 --> 00:16:45.471
He's remembering the moment
that Giraffe died.

00:16:46.605 --> 00:16:48.507
<i>Give him back! Zebra!</i>

00:16:49.241 --> 00:16:50.342
<i>Come over here!</i>

00:16:50.642 --> 00:16:53.278
Shit. And then what?

00:16:53.612 --> 00:16:55.180
What did Giraffe say?

00:16:58.283 --> 00:17:01.153
<i>I have it now. I can do you in with this.</i>

00:17:01.687 --> 00:17:04.189
<i>This is a stone</i>
<i>that will return time to you!</i>

00:17:06.792 --> 00:17:08.193
<i>Now, hand Zebra over to me!</i>

00:17:10.162 --> 00:17:11.063
<i>Zebra!</i>

00:17:39.324 --> 00:17:42.394
<i>When the Gate exploded,</i>
<i>a vast amount of energy...</i>

00:17:43.062 --> 00:17:45.197
and an imaginary coordinate system
were created

00:17:45.564 --> 00:17:47.433
from the resulting twists in hyperspace,

00:17:48.067 --> 00:17:50.335
and got enclosed in the gem in this ring.

00:17:52.071 --> 00:17:56.575
And that same energy
broke Wenn's circadian rhythm.

00:17:57.376 --> 00:18:00.546
His pineal gland continually produces
a substance

00:18:00.612 --> 00:18:03.148
similar to melatonin that inhibits aging.

00:18:03.816 --> 00:18:07.553
That's how the theory goes, in a nutshell.

00:18:08.353 --> 00:18:10.556
-You understand?
-Like I do.

00:18:11.623 --> 00:18:12.491
I don't either.

00:18:12.858 --> 00:18:16.128
So, in other words,
there's no way to do it for sure...

00:18:16.662 --> 00:18:19.098
other than to stick that gem into Wenn.

00:18:23.402 --> 00:18:25.137
I don't know what will happen.

00:18:25.437 --> 00:18:27.573
It might explode
the moment you shoot it in.

00:18:28.607 --> 00:18:30.175
This makes me excited.

00:18:39.618 --> 00:18:40.486
What?

00:18:41.220 --> 00:18:43.355
I thought this might be
the last time I see you,

00:18:43.422 --> 00:18:44.890
so I thought I'd see you off.

00:18:46.692 --> 00:18:49.661
-So, you're finally gonna leave us?
-No. You aren't coming back.

00:18:59.404 --> 00:19:00.472
I don't like it.

00:19:01.373 --> 00:19:02.474
I don't like it one bit.

00:19:11.917 --> 00:19:13.585
Men are such idiots.

00:21:37.062 --> 00:21:38.063
I see.

00:21:38.964 --> 00:21:40.766
I can finally die now.

00:21:43.568 --> 00:21:45.337
I feel so heavy.

00:21:47.539 --> 00:21:50.709
But... I feel so at ease now.

00:21:52.344 --> 00:21:53.312
Do you know?

00:21:55.947 --> 00:21:59.818
Do you understand? Do you?

00:22:15.567 --> 00:22:16.668
Like I do.

00:24:18.223 --> 00:24:21.793
<i>-Hey, do you know what heavy metal is?!</i>
<i>-What? I didn't catch that!</i>

00:24:21.860 --> 00:24:24.663
<i>-Heavy metal! I said, heavy metal!</i>
<i>-What did you say?</i>

00:24:24.729 --> 00:24:27.098
<i>Hey, can you do something</i>
<i>about this racket?!</i>

00:24:27.165 --> 00:24:29.668
<i>This is in the background</i>
<i>during the entire next episode!</i>

00:24:29.734 --> 00:24:32.938
<i>-Maybe I shouldn't appear then!</i>
<i>-I can't hear a thing you're saying!</i>

00:24:33.004 --> 00:24:34.940
<i>Next episode: "Heavy Metal Queen!"</i>

00:24:35.006 --> 00:24:37.042
<i>Are you sure they can really hear us?!</i>

